# Line-ending + binary normalization.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.stl binary

# --- Generated but TRACKED files: stay committed, stay out of the way ---
# Three tiers, from two git/GitHub knobs:
#   linguist-generated=true  (GitHub): collapse in a PR's Files-changed (one click expands) + drop from the
#                            repo language bar. The diff stays REACHABLE.
#   -diff                    (git):    treat as binary -> no textual diff anywhere (local or GitHub). Hidden.
#   merge=union              (git):    on conflict keep BOTH sides. Safe ONLY for line-oriented files
#                            regenerated wholesale (a stray dup line self-heals next regen); CORRUPTS
#                            structured files (json object / toml) — never union those.
#
# tier 1 — churny line file you never read by hand (fully hidden + auto-merged):
.beads/issues.jsonl            -diff linguist-generated=true merge=union
# tier 3 — generated, but its diff is the architecture-erosion signal when you want it (collapsed, expandable,
# regenerate on conflict — never union a JSON object):
docs/architecture/graph.json   linguist-generated=true
